is known only from the holotype collection, which was collected sometime in 2004 (
<bibRefCitation id="B6B7ECB7D2486EA1EF14531140584CC6" author="Amey, J" journalOrPublisher="New Zealand Journal of Botany" pageId="111" pageNumber="112" pagination="87 - 90" publicationUrl="10.1080/00288250709509705" refId="B4" refString="Amey, J, Lord, JM, de Lange, P, 2007. First record of a vascular plant from the Bounty Islands: Lepidium oleraceum (nau, Cook's scurvy grass) (Brassicaceae). New Zealand Journal of Botany 45: 87 - 90, 10.1080/00288250709509705" title="First record of a vascular plant from the Bounty Islands: Lepidium oleraceum (nau, Cook's scurvy grass) (Brassicaceae)." url="10.1080/00288250709509705" volume="45" year="2007">Amey et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
